\begin{aligned}
&\text{The line element in the primed (rim-adapted) coordinates is:} \\[1em]
&ds^2 = \left(-c^2 + r'^2\omega^2\right)dt'^2 + dr'^2 + 2 r'^2 \omega\, d\theta'\, dt' + r'^2 (d\theta')^2 \\[1.5em]
&\text{The metric components are:} \\
&\hspace{2em}
g_{\mu\nu} =
\begin{pmatrix}
    -c^2 + r'^2\omega^2 & 0 & r'^2\omega \\
    0 & 1 & 0 \\
    r'^2\omega & 0 & r'^2
\end{pmatrix}
\end{aligned}
